Speaking after receiving a dummy cheque of 60m/-in Dar es Salaam yesterday, she said the Tatu Mzuka lottery could boost their capital particularly at the current time when they face financial challenges. "Some of us face many challenges which affect our businesses. During hard financial times, Tatu Mzuka can be our saviour," a vividly elated Ms Mtewele said. The Tatu Mzuka spokesperson, Kemi Mutahaba said that the lottery has changed lives of many Tanzanians including businessmen and women, students, house wives, house girls and others in the community.